 Issele-Uku, Rev. Fr Charles Uganwa said the hoodlums were talking with some of the Church parishioners. Agwameseh, however, said the Catholic church does not pay ransom for their abducted Priest, pleading with the abductors to release the Clergy unconditionally for the sake of God. He added that the church does not have money for the payment of ransom. As at the time of filing this report,  effort was still being made to reach the Police authority in the state for comment on the matter. Vanguard News Nigeria TENSION is mounting in Ogodor kingdom, Aniocha North Local Government Area, Delta State, following the abduction of the traditional ruler of the kingdom, HRM Sunday Olisewokwu by suspected Fulani herdsmen. June 4, 2018 In "News" *We'll get them, rescue victim—POLICE  By Festus Ahon ASABA—THREE days after Rev. Fr. Jude Onyebadi, Parish Priest of SS Peter and Paul Catholic Church, Issele-Azagba, Delta State, was kidnapped by suspected herdsmen, the abductors have reportedly demanded a N20 million ransom. The cleric, it was gathered, was kidnapped by three… December 20, 2016 In "News" TENSION is mounting in Ogodor Kingdom, Aniocha North Local Government Area, Delta State, following the abduction of the traditional ruler of the kingdom, His Royal Majesty, Sunday Olisewokwu, by herdsmen. June 5, 2018 In "Crime Guard"